Machine                  — Physical hardware of the computer (OSI Layer 1)
 ├─ CPU                  — Central Processing Unit, executes instructions (Layer 1)
 │   ├─ Core             — Physical CPU core (Layer 1)
 │   │   └─ Thread       — Logical execution unit / hyperthread (Layer 1)
 │
 ├─ Memory               — RAM, temporary data storage (Layer 1)
 │
 └─ NIC                  — Network Interface Card, handles network I/O (Layer 1/2)
     └─ Queue            — Hardware queue for packets (Layer 2)

Process                  — Running REST API server application (Layer 7 / Application)
 ├─ Thread               — Execution unit inside server (Layer 7)
 │   └─ Core             — CPU core scheduled to run thread (Layer 1)
 │
 ├─ Memory               — Virtual address space of server (Layer 7)
 │
 └─ Socket               — Endpoint for incoming/outgoing connections (Layer 4 / Transport)
     ├─ Port             — Number identifying API service (e.g., 80, 443) (Layer 4)
     └─ Address          — IP address bound to socket (Layer 3 / Network)

Network                  — Communication and data transport
 ├─ Transport Protocol   — TCP (reliable, connection-oriented) (Layer 4)
 ├─ Application Protocol — HTTP/HTTPS for REST API, JSON or XML data (Layer 7)
 ├─ Packet               — Unit of data transmitted over network (Layer 3/4)
 └─ Connection           — Established TCP session between client and server (Layer 4)

REST API Layer           — Logical representation of API communication
 ├─ Endpoint             — URL path exposed by server (Layer 7)
 ├─ Method               — HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE) (Layer 7)
 ├─ Request              — Data sent by client (Layer 7)
 ├─ Response             — Data sent back by server (Layer 7)
 └─ Headers / Body       — Metadata and content of API request/response (Layer 7)

OSI Layers (for reference)
 ├─ Layer 1 Physical      — Hardware, CPU, Memory, NIC
 ├─ Layer 2 Data Link     — NIC queues, MAC addressing
 ├─ Layer 3 Network       — IP addresses, routing, packets
 ├─ Layer 4 Transport     — Socket, Port, TCP, Connection
 ├─ Layer 5 Session       — TCP session management
 ├─ Layer 6 Presentation  — Data serialization / encoding (JSON, XML)
 └─ Layer 7 Application   — REST API server, HTTP, Endpoints, Methods, Headers/Body

